<subSubSection id="52956573CC15C131FF7EFE70FC1FFE3F" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC15C131FF7EFE70FC1FFE3F" blockId="23.[151,1437,295,554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FF7EFE70FECFFE56" bold="true" box="[197,327,411,437]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FE75FE77FD4EFE56" box="[462,710,412,437]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FE75FE77FD4EFE56" box="[462,710,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Afrasura amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with four spurs on the hindlegs (two in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FB62FE77FAD7FE56" box="[1241,1375,412,437]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FB62FE77FAD7FE56" box="[1241,1375,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and male forewing underside costal base dark (yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FCB8FE29FC0FFE38" box="[771,903,450,475]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FCB8FE29FC0FFE38" box="[771,903,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="52956573CC15C131FF7EFE03FB4BFDC9" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC15C131FF7EFE03FB4BFDC9" blockId="23.[151,1437,295,554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FF7EFE03FEC8FDE1" bold="true" box="[197,320,488,514]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FE74FE02FD41FDE1" box="[463,713,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FE74FE02FD41FDE1" box="[463,713,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Afrasura amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FD62FE02FCD4FDE1" box="[729,860,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FD62FE02FCD4FDE1" box="[729,860,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FCD7FE02FBB7FDE1" box="[876,1087,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FCD7FE02FBB7FDE1" box="[876,1087,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FBC0FE02FA8CFDE1" box="[1147,1284,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FBC0FE02FA8CFDE1" box="[1147,1284,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar in genitalic morphology; the group is East African except for 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC15C131FCF0FDFBFC20FDCA" box="[843,936,528,553]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC15C131FCF0FDFBFC20FDCA" box="[843,936,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is West African.
</paragraph>
